title.narrative: # of service providers engaged in Climate Smart Services

20% of CBSPs produce seeds of early maturing crop varieties and 70 CBSPs produce pulse seeds, fodder seeds and seedlings, and/or fruit seedlings; 40 farmers groups engaged in certified seed production for forage species; volume of forage seeds certified and marketed; 330 well drilling service providers provide well drilling services in 55 woredas; and 200 primary cooperatives distribute blended/ compound fertilizer to farmers.

title.narrative: Greening road map updated, approved and implemented
# of woredas promoting IPM technologies on IPM-FFS modalities and # of woredas with web-based, community pest early warning and forecasting system established /strengthened

Integrated Pest Management (IPM) technologies piloted using IPM-FFS modalities in 3 woredas for Maize Lethal Necrotic Disease (MLND) and scaled up in all mid to lower altitude maize growing woredas of Oromia and SNNPR where there is MLND problem and web-based community pest early warning and forecasting system established/strengthened in 100 woredas.

comment.narrative: IPM technologies implemented only by few farmers and web-based community pest early warning and forecasting system not established
